title: Lables - exchange label text is too low on label
text: Click on Screen with Wrench button. Choose store and machine, then click Change this machine only Scroll down to Adv. Configuration and click it Scroll down to PrintSmallHeaderOnChangeLables and set it to 1. This reduces the size of the logo/text. Scroll down to bottom of page and click Save and Close.
description:
Click on Screen with Wrench button. 

  

 

  

Choose store and machine, then click Change this machine only 

  

 

  

Scroll down to Adv. Configuration and click it 

  

 

  

Scroll down to PrintSmallHeaderOnChangeLables and set it to 1. This reduces the size of the logo/text. 

  

 

  

Scroll down to bottom of page and click Save and Close.

title: Lables - number to be printed is 0
text: If number of labels is set to zero when they want to accept an invoice, this can be changed in Backoffice Support Tools if the prices are KVM. First check which pricing system the client uses. DdD Backoffice Support Tools -> Client Information Serach for and show client Scroll down to General and check what price priority the client has: If it says KVM, then click Menu to go back to the startpage of Support Tools -> Edit/create system -> Find client If there is a tick under No labels at receipt of goods, then remove it and click update client, then reload the POS. This should fix the problem. If it says VKM or MVK, then open Backoffice for the client -> Maintenance -> Supplier Remove the tick under Filter -> OK -> Reload POS
description:
If number of labels is set to zero when they want to accept an invoice, this can be changed in Backoffice Support Tools if the prices are KVM. 

  

First check which pricing system the client uses. 

  

DdD Backoffice Support Tools -> Client Information 

  

 

  

Serach for and show client 

  

 

  

Scroll down to General and check what price priority the client has: 

  

 

  

If it says KVM, then click Menu to go back to the startpage of Support Tools -> Edit/create system -> Find client 

  

 

  

If there is a tick under No labels at receipt of goods, then remove it and click update client, then reload the POS. This should fix the problem. 

  

If it says VKM or MVK, then open Backoffice for the client -> Maintenance -> Supplier 

  

 

  

Remove the tick under Filter -> OK -> Reload POS

title: Labels - setup is wrong (Citizen printer CLP-521)
text: Labels print wrong (over two labels): There at two blue wheels inside the printer. The little one (media thickness) should be on 0 (Zero) The big one (media width) should be on 9 Manual
description:
Labels print wrong (over two labels): 

  

There at two blue wheels inside the printer. 

  

The little one (media thickness) should be on 0 (Zero) 

The big one (media width) should be on 9 

  

  

Manual

title: Labels directly from POS.
text: The customer sometime requests if it is possible to print a price label based on the barcode directly from POS menu (e.g Genvej,Funktioner/may be create a button) as they have to print a lot of price labels everyday. We must note that there are only two possibilities to print labels. The first option is one can print labels individually from the POS by seraching for an item and then print a price tag from the search page as shown. Remember one must enter at least 5 characters in order to search for an item on the basis of different parametres as article number,Article,Season, Colour etc. The second possiblilty is to print it from the backoffice as shown below.
